==O==

{{glossary}}
<span id="oasis"></span>{{term|term='''[[oasis]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=}}

<span id="ocean"></span>{{term|term='''[[ocean]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=A vast, contiguous body of salt water covering more than 70% of the Earth's surface area and surrounding the {{gli|continent|continental}} landmasses, or a portion of this larger body of water that is divided and distinguished from the other portions, each of which is called an ocean, by the presence of the landmasses.<ref name="OERI 1996"/>}}

<span id="open range"></span>{{term|term='''[[open range]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=A cattle- or sheep-ranching area characterized by a general absence of fences and in which livestock are allowed to roam freely.<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

<span id="ordinal directions"></span>{{term|term='''[[ordinal directions]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=See ''{{gli|intercardinal directions}}''.}}

{{term|term='''[[orographic rainfall]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=Precipitation that results when moist air is lifted over a topographic barrier, such as a mountain range.<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

<span id="outwash"></span>{{term|term='''[[outwash]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=Rocky and sandy surface material deposited by melted water that flows from a {{gli|glacier}}.<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

{{term|term='''[[overburden]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=Material covering a mineral seam or bed that must be removed before the mineral can be removed in [[strip mining]].<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

<span id="oxbow"></span>{{term|term='''[[oxbow lake|oxbow]]'''}}
{{defn|no=1|defn=A wide U-shaped {{gli|meander}} in a {{gli|river}} or {{gli|stream}}.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn=The {{gli|lake}} formed when a meander is [[meander cutoff|cut off]] from the {{gli|main stem}} of the river, creating a separate body of water.}}

{{glossary end}}

